## HTML Structure

The Waiting For page should follow the same patterns as Next Actions and Projects. Here's the recommended HTML skeleton:

```html
{% extends "base.html" %}
{% block title %}Waiting For -- Todo List{% endblock %}
{% block nav %}{% include "gtd_nav.html" %}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="waiting-for">
    <h1>Waiting For</h1>

    {% if let Some(error) = error_message %}
    <div class="waiting-for__error" role="alert">{{ error }}</div>
    {% endif %}

    <!-- Add form: title + waiting_on text -->
    <form method="post" action="/waiting-for" class="waiting-for__add" ...htmx attrs...>
        <label for="waiting-for-title">Add waiting for item</label>
        <div class="waiting-for__add-row">
            <input type="text" id="waiting-for-title" name="title" 
                   placeholder="What are you waiting for?"
                   maxlength="300" autocomplete="off"
                   class="waiting-for__add-input">
            <label for="waiting-for-contact" class="waiting-for__contact-label">From</label>
            <input type="text" id="waiting-for-contact" name="waiting_on"
                   placeholder="Who/what?"
                   maxlength="300" autocomplete="off"
                   class="waiting-for__add-contact">
            <button type="submit" class="waiting-for__add-submit">Add</button>
        </div>
    </form>

    <!-- Empty state -->
    {% if items.is_empty() %}
    <div class="waiting-for__empty-state">
        <p>Nothing pending from others. When you delegate something or need to follow up, add it here.</p>
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    <!-- Item list -->
    <ul class="waiting-for__list" role="list" id="waiting-for-list" ...>
        {% for item in items %}
        {% include "waiting_for_item.html" %}
        {% endfor %}
    </ul>
</div>
{% endblock %}
```

## Each Waiting For Item

Key difference from next-actions: each item shows **who/what** (the `waiting_on` field) and **date added**. The metadata should be semantically associated, not just visually adjacent. The user story says "Each item's 'waiting on' metadata is associated with the item (not just visual proximity)."

```html
<li class="waiting-for-item" id="waiting-for-{{ item.id }}">
    <div class="waiting-for-item__content">
        <span class="waiting-for-item__title">{{ item.title }}</span>
        <span class="waiting-for-item__meta">
            <span class="waiting-for-item__contact">{{ item.waiting_on }}</span>
            <span class="waiting-for-item__date">
                <time datetime="{{ item.created_at }}">{{ format_date }}</time>
            </span>
        </span>
    </div>
    <!-- action buttons: resolve, edit, delete -->
</li>
```

## CSS Classes and Tokens

Follow these established conventions. All values from design tokens -- **no hardcoded hex or pixel values**.

```css
/* ---- Waiting For ---- */
.waiting-for {
    padding-block-start: var(--space-lg);
}

.waiting-for h1 {
    margin-block-end: var(--space-lg);
}

.waiting-for__error {
    background-color: var(--color-danger-light);
    color: var(--color-danger);
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-md);
}

/* Add form -- follows the inbox-capture / projects__add pattern */
.waiting-for__add {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: end;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-lg);
}

.waiting-for__add label:first-child {
    inline-size: 100%;
    margin-block-end: var(--space-xs);
}

.waiting-for__add-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    inline-size: 100%;
}

.waiting-for__add-input {
    flex: 1;
    min-inline-size: 10rem;
}

.waiting-for__contact-label {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    font-weight: var(--font-medium);
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
}

.waiting-for__add-contact {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    min-inline-size: 8rem;
}

.waiting-for__add-submit {
    flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* Item list */
.waiting-for__list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
}

.waiting-for-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    padding-block: var(--space-sm);
    padding-inline: var(--space-sm);
    border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

.waiting-for-item:first-child {
    border-block-start: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

.waiting-for-item__content {
    flex: 1;
    min-inline-size: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
}

.waiting-for-item__title {
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
}

.waiting-for-item__meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-xs) var(--space-sm);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
}

.waiting-for-item__contact {
    /* "From: person" pill badge like context badges */
    padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-sm);
    background-color: var(--color-gray-100);
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
}

.waiting-for-item__date {
    padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-sm);
}

